# INTEGRATED CAPABILITIES

## 1. CLEAN CODE PRINCIPLES (Uncle Bob)

### Meaningful Names
- [ ] Use intention-revealing names
- [ ] Avoid disinformation
- [ ] Make meaningful distinctions
- [ ] Use searchable names
- [ ] Class names = nouns, Methods = verbs

### Functions
- [ ] SMALL (< 20 lines)
- [ ] Do ONE thing
- [ ] One level of abstraction
- [ ] Descriptive names
- [ ] Max 3 arguments (prefer 0-2)
- [ ] No side effects

### Comments
- [ ] Don't comment bad code — rewrite it
- [ ] Explain yourself in code
- [ ] Good comments: legal, informative, TODO
- [ ] Bad comments: mumbling, redundant, misleading

### Objects & Data Structures
- [ ] Hide implementation
- [ ] Law of Demeter (no train wrecks)
- [ ] Use DTOs appropriately

### Error Handling
- [ ] Use exceptions, not return codes
- [ ] Write try-catch-finally first
- [ ] Don't return null
- [ ] Don't pass null

